        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "If multiple requests are made in the same process (cron job) that involve headers being sent to Amazon Web Services it wil barf. This is due to the TRUE parameter not being set in the _makeRequest method on line 554 of Zend_Service_Amazon_S3. The resetParameters call is trying to clean up the static Zend_Http_Client but without it being passed true it will not clean up the headers properly."
        },
